TaskDescription: This checklist outlines the responsibilities and equipment operating procedures to be performed by the ASE 1 on the RIVET JOINT Baseline 12 aircraft.

Objectives.Description: Setup actors to default, should be hidden
1. Review AFTO Form 781s
Objectives.SubDescription:
Do not energize any equipment that has a Red X condition
Notify crew of any conditions affecting mission accomplishment

Args: Open Floating Menu to Review AFTO Form 781s

Objectives.Description:
NOTE
Maintenance Station
Objectives.SubDescription:
As all recon area TRs are tied on a common power bus, load meter readings should be approximately equal at all times. Unequal or zero load meter readings are indicative of possible TR malfunctions.
If any recon area TR fails, the load meters on the Mission Power Control Panel must be monitored and 28 VDC power must be managed. Attempt to reduce the non-essential DC load of the remaining TR units to prevent a possible overload condition.

Actors.OverrideMainText:
<LargeText>NOTE:</>

 <SmallText>As all recon area TRs are tied on a common power bus, load meter readings should be approximately equal at all times. Unequal or zero load meter readings are indicative of possible TR malfunctions.</>
 <SmallText>If any recon area TR fails, the load meters on the Mission Power Control Panel must be monitored and 28 VDC power must be managed. Attempt to reduce the non-essential DC load of the remaining TR units to prevent a possible overload condition.</>

Objectives.SubDescription: Pick up with grip button and pull towards your face

Objectives.Description: 25A3 cont. Tighten mask to avoid mask fogging
Objectives.SubDescription: Tighten mask at back of head with the 'interact' button

Objectives.Description: 25A4. Switch Diluter Lever to 100% Oxygen (UP)

Objectives.SubDescription: Note: Flow is shown as white on indicator

Objectives.Description: 25A6 cont. While holding Toggle Lever to TEST MASK, verify no flow around mask

Actors.OverrideMainText: Verify no flow around mask

Objectives.Description: 25A7. Switch Toggle Lever to EMERGENCY (UP)

Objectives.SubDescription:
Indicator should alternate between black and white
Release button to simulate holding breath; a white indicator when breath is held indicates a leak

Objectives.Description: 25A9. Switch Diluter Lever to NORMAL OXYGEN (DOWN)
25A10. Check for no flow while holding breath
Objectives.SubDescription: Note: Flow is shown as white on indicator

Objectives.Description: 25A11. Switch Toggle Lever to NORMAL (Middle)
